1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:52,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:56,278 --> 00:00:59,073
FILING FOR LOVE

3
00:01:06,330 --> 00:01:08,123
How could you miss something
this mundane?

4
00:01:08,374 --> 00:01:10,334
Not even a rookie would do this.
Get a hold of yourself!

5
00:01:11,001 --> 00:01:13,045
Order within an organization
is built on rank.

6
00:01:18,884 --> 00:01:19,927
However...

7
00:01:21,970 --> 00:01:23,764
the true power game between these two

8
00:01:24,598 --> 00:01:26,100
goes much deeper

9
00:01:26,725 --> 00:01:27,768
and far more quietly.

10
00:01:37,361 --> 00:01:39,363
TECHNICAL HIGH SCHOOL

11
00:01:45,619 --> 00:01:47,246
Does a completely equal relationship

12
00:01:47,830 --> 00:01:48,914
even exist?

13
00:01:58,424 --> 00:02:01,385
When two or more come together,
a hierarchy forms.

14
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:07,266
Even between friends and lovers

15
00:02:07,891 --> 00:02:09,727
an imbalance of power is
almost inevitable.

16
00:02:22,573 --> 00:02:23,657
And everyone

17
00:02:24,450 --> 00:02:26,910
desires to rise higher,
even if only a little.

18
00:02:28,579 --> 00:02:29,580
Good job, everyone.

19
00:02:29,663 --> 00:02:30,706
Sometimes

20
00:02:31,373 --> 00:02:33,083
at the risk of doing things
they shouldn't.

21
00:02:35,085 --> 00:02:36,837
Gosh, that tastes so sweet.

22
00:02:41,008 --> 00:02:42,050
What's that?

23
00:02:42,468 --> 00:02:43,510
- What's what?
- What is it?

24
00:02:45,262 --> 00:02:46,972
- Something's hovering outside.
- Where?

25
00:02:47,055 --> 00:02:48,056
You see something?

26
00:02:55,898 --> 00:02:57,357
You're quite photogenic

27
00:02:57,441 --> 00:02:58,442
Director Kang.

28
00:03:08,243 --> 00:03:09,286
Are you the police?

29
00:03:09,995 --> 00:03:10,996
No, I'm not.

30
00:03:13,207 --> 00:03:14,291
I'm...

31
00:03:49,576 --> 00:03:50,619
NOH KI-JUN

32
00:03:52,871 --> 00:03:54,581
I'm with the Audit Team
at the head office.

33
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:57,167
Stop what you were doing
and follow me for a chat

34
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:59,336
Director Kang.

35
00:04:02,589 --> 00:04:04,758
INTERVIEW ROOM
AUDIT IN PROGRESS

36
00:04:14,893 --> 00:04:18,772
I heard Haemu's Audit Team
can bring down birds in flight.

37
00:04:20,691 --> 00:04:22,234
I see you send your own birds now.

38
00:04:22,317 --> 00:04:23,986
And you're about to crash and burn.

39
00:04:24,236 --> 00:04:25,612
- Hey, you!
- It's Assistant Manager Noh

40
00:04:25,696 --> 00:04:26,697
from Audit Team One.

41
00:04:26,780 --> 00:04:28,866
How dare an assistant manager
harass a director?

42
00:04:29,449 --> 00:04:30,576
Do you think you're the police?

43
00:04:31,159 --> 00:04:32,286
The National Intelligence Service?

44
00:04:32,578 --> 00:04:34,454
This is illegal filming.

45
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:38,792
I'll sue you and your whole team
for invasion of privacy.

46
00:04:42,212 --> 00:04:45,507
It's the least I can do to catch
a spy who's selling core tech

47
00:04:46,550 --> 00:04:47,593
to an overseas competitor.

48
00:04:48,802 --> 00:04:50,470
We have our own struggles, too.

49
00:04:50,762 --> 00:04:52,639
It's always the unethical ones
who are obsessed

50
00:04:53,765 --> 00:04:56,518
with privacy and personal rights.

51
00:04:59,479 --> 00:05:00,522
Hey, listen.

52
00:05:01,732 --> 00:05:03,066
Don't go too far.

53
00:05:03,859 --> 00:05:07,279
Even if I were an industrial spy,
this is just my first offense.

54
00:05:07,362 --> 00:05:09,281
So if I act remorseful

55
00:05:09,364 --> 00:05:11,575
I'll most likely be let off
on probation.

56
00:05:17,539 --> 00:05:18,624
Director Kang.

57
00:05:18,707 --> 00:05:20,292
He speaks pretty good Korean,
didn't he?

58
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:21,835
Because he's an ethnic Korean
from China.

59
00:05:21,919 --> 00:05:23,337
You could say he's Korean.

60
00:05:24,463 --> 00:05:26,965
A North Korean.

61
00:05:32,721 --> 00:05:35,349
Turns out this company was
a source of funding for North Korea.

62
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:37,768
It was disguised
as a foreign-currency operation

63
00:05:38,852 --> 00:05:40,646
but it was actually run
by North Korea.

64
00:05:43,231 --> 00:05:44,232
Oh, dear.

65
00:05:46,401 --> 00:05:48,737
If you're charged with espionage,
that means

66
00:05:50,656 --> 00:05:53,408
you're not an industrial spy anymore
but an actual spy.

67
00:05:54,534 --> 00:05:55,577
Probation?

68
00:05:57,704 --> 00:05:59,790
You'll most likely go to prison.

69
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:02,501
Darn it.

70
00:06:10,842 --> 00:06:12,552
- Oh, no.
- Don't do that.

71
00:06:13,136 --> 00:06:14,471
Will you calm down?

72
00:06:14,554 --> 00:06:16,098
This is so infuriating!

73
00:06:16,473 --> 00:06:19,601
You punks. I said it wasn't me.
Why won't you believe me?

74
00:06:19,685 --> 00:06:22,062
- Calm down, sir. We got a tip-off...
- "Calm down"?

75
00:06:22,312 --> 00:06:24,773
- We got a tip-off.
- A tip-off? What tip-off?

76
00:06:24,898 --> 00:06:26,858
I'm being framed, okay?

77
00:06:27,317 --> 00:06:29,403
Something's always going on
at Team Three.

78
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:31,363
What is it this time?

79
00:06:31,905 --> 00:06:34,408
Someone sent an anonymous note
to Team Three saying

80
00:06:34,491 --> 00:06:36,535
he hid the fact that he was married
and approached her.

81
00:06:36,618 --> 00:06:39,287
As proof, she said
he has a mole down there.

82
00:06:39,579 --> 00:06:40,914
- What?
- Down there.

83
00:06:40,998 --> 00:06:41,999
Right there.

84
00:06:45,836 --> 00:06:46,878
Haemu Group.

85
00:06:47,754 --> 00:06:49,965
The 7th largest business in Korea
and 9th in sales.

86
00:06:50,549 --> 00:06:52,342
The top-ranking department

87
00:06:52,426 --> 00:06:54,177
in this conglomerate
with 42 subsidiaries.

88
00:06:55,012 --> 00:06:56,388
Even the head office's Audit Team

89
00:06:56,805 --> 00:06:58,765
has a hierarchy of its own.

90
00:07:00,142 --> 00:07:01,935
Audit Team One and Two

91
00:07:02,019 --> 00:07:04,312
handle major cases
such as embezzlement

92
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:08,191
malpractice, collusion,
and information leaks.

93
00:07:09,901 --> 00:07:10,944
Audit Team Three...

94
00:07:11,028 --> 00:07:13,155
I'm not in the mood for coffee!

95
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,906
Okay, fine. Get your hands off me.

96
00:07:14,990 --> 00:07:16,158
- Hands off.
- Okay.

97
00:07:16,241 --> 00:07:17,534
I'll show you.

98
00:07:17,617 --> 00:07:19,077
- No, don't!
- No, don't!

99
00:07:21,163 --> 00:07:22,164
No!

100
00:07:22,247 --> 00:07:23,248
Don't!

101
00:07:23,665 --> 00:07:24,750
Shoot.

102
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:26,960
- Look!
- Oh, come on...

103
00:07:27,377 --> 00:07:28,420
Look carefully.

104
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,464
Do you see a mole?

105
00:07:30,547 --> 00:07:31,882
- Don't cover it.
- What's his issue?

106
00:07:32,340 --> 00:07:33,383
I'm innocent.

107
00:07:33,675 --> 00:07:35,969
This is what they do.

108
00:07:41,683 --> 00:07:45,604
EPISODE 1:
UP&amp;DOWN

109
00:08:18,303 --> 00:08:19,971
Hello, sir. Good morning.

110
00:08:20,138 --> 00:08:22,891
If it isn't Noh Ki-jun,
the gentleman.

111
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:25,977
You're having
a handsome start to the day.

112
00:08:26,269 --> 00:08:27,354
Thank you.

113
00:08:27,437 --> 00:08:29,022
- Have a great day.
- You, too.

114
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:49,126
SAFEGUARDING CORE TECHNOLOGY

115
00:08:49,209 --> 00:08:50,293
FROM INDUSTRIAL SPIES

116
00:08:50,377 --> 00:08:51,878
HAEMU'S AUDIT TEAM

117
00:08:52,462 --> 00:08:55,257
Auditing increases
and improves the value

118
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:57,050
of the company's business execution.

119
00:08:59,177 --> 00:09:01,471
NOH KI-JUN AKA MR. SMILES,
ASSISTANT MANAGER, AUDIT TEAM 1

120
00:09:02,514 --> 00:09:03,765
Oh, wow.

121
00:09:05,892 --> 00:09:06,893
"Mr. Smiles"?

122
00:09:06,977 --> 00:09:08,353
We can't have those
in the Audit Team.

123
00:09:08,436 --> 00:09:10,438
I didn't come up with it, okay?

124
00:09:10,856 --> 00:09:12,691
What's wrong with it?
It gives me pride

125
00:09:12,774 --> 00:09:15,193
that my colleague is
the face of the Audit Team.

126
00:09:16,153 --> 00:09:19,072
To be honest, Team Three yesterday
was a huge embarrassment.

127
00:09:19,156 --> 00:09:20,991
They let a guy
drop his pants in the office.

128
00:09:21,074 --> 00:09:23,160
It was utter madness.

129
00:09:23,243 --> 00:09:24,411
I dreamed of it, even.

130
00:09:24,494 --> 00:09:26,329
That guy's thing.

131
00:09:26,997 --> 00:09:28,790
- Oh, the shudders.
- Get out of my head.

132
00:09:32,544 --> 00:09:34,796
- It's just gimbap.
- Sorry. My bad.

133
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,339
- Sorry.
- Anyway...

134
00:09:36,423 --> 00:09:39,426
Why should we handle stuff like that?
It's not at all dignified.

135
00:09:39,509 --> 00:09:41,219
We must look into everything
we get a tip-off on.

136
00:09:41,303 --> 00:09:43,263
That's why we have Team Three.

137
00:09:43,346 --> 00:09:45,140
Team One and Two
do all the important stuff

138
00:09:45,223 --> 00:09:47,017
and Team Three
gets the trivial stuff.

139
00:09:47,392 --> 00:09:48,852
They go on stakeouts

140
00:09:48,935 --> 00:09:51,771
to see how long people smoke
and poop during work hours.

141
00:09:51,855 --> 00:09:53,732
Once I saw them go around
all the break rooms

142
00:09:53,815 --> 00:09:55,692
to count the coffee mix packets.

143
00:09:56,651 --> 00:09:57,861
That's so depressing.

144
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:00,238
People think our Audit Team
is powerful enough

145
00:10:00,322 --> 00:10:01,698
to bring down birds from the sky.

146
00:10:01,781 --> 00:10:04,117
- Team Three...
- Not Team Three.

147
00:10:04,659 --> 00:10:06,494
They're more like poop-scoops.

148
00:10:07,454 --> 00:10:08,914
I like the ring of that. Poop-scoops.

149
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:12,918
What if someone were to hear you?

150
00:10:13,543 --> 00:10:14,544
It's Executive Assistant Park.

151
00:10:22,344 --> 00:10:23,470
- Gosh.
- My word.

152
00:10:23,553 --> 00:10:25,847
Hello, Ms. Park.
Isn't it a lovely day?

153
00:10:27,891 --> 00:10:28,975
It is.

154
00:10:30,268 --> 00:10:32,020
We got to see her before work.

155
00:10:32,103 --> 00:10:33,897
I have a good feeling about today.

156
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:36,483
I'll go ahead.
You guys finish breakfast.

157
00:10:36,775 --> 00:10:38,276
What? You're going already?

158
00:11:00,423 --> 00:11:02,008
What's my afternoon schedule?

159
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:05,053
You have a meeting
with Haemu Media's executives.

160
00:11:14,104 --> 00:11:15,313
I like your tie.

161
00:11:21,528 --> 00:11:23,113
You have a good eye, sir.

162
00:12:00,108 --> 00:12:01,484
- Ki-jun.
- Hey.

163
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:18,251
Ki-jun.

164
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:20,879
Our team saw the PR clip,
and everyone's raving

165
00:12:20,962 --> 00:12:22,797
and wondering who you are.

166
00:12:23,381 --> 00:12:25,717
Really? They'll swoon
if they see me in person.

167
00:12:26,801 --> 00:12:28,887
What are you doing today after work?

168
00:12:29,304 --> 00:12:30,388
How about a drink?

169
00:12:30,472 --> 00:12:32,891
I heard a nice wine bar
opened nearby.

170
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:35,435
- Where is it?
- It's called...

171
00:12:46,488 --> 00:12:48,239
I'll be in touch, okay?

172
00:12:48,323 --> 00:12:49,491
Wait, Ki-jun.

173
00:12:50,408 --> 00:12:51,993
14TH FLOOR
PLANNING TEAM, AUDIT TEAM

174
00:13:00,418 --> 00:13:01,503
What the heck?

175
00:13:08,676 --> 00:13:09,719
Ji-hye...

176
00:13:12,597 --> 00:13:14,974
That's way too passionate a greeting
after a long break.

177
00:13:16,393 --> 00:13:17,769
I missed you.

178
00:13:18,937 --> 00:13:20,522
Will you meet up
with that other girl later?

179
00:13:20,855 --> 00:13:21,898
Hang out with me.

180
00:13:24,275 --> 00:13:26,319
No, wait. What?

181
00:13:29,489 --> 00:13:30,615
Aren't you getting married?

182
00:13:31,991 --> 00:13:33,034
You called it off?

183
00:13:33,118 --> 00:13:34,119
Not exactly.

184
00:13:34,994 --> 00:13:36,329
I feel a bit down.

185
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:40,583
The idea that I'll be stuck
with one guy for the rest of my life.

186
00:13:43,420 --> 00:13:44,504
How about

187
00:13:45,755 --> 00:13:48,633
we have a good time
just one last time?

188
00:13:55,515 --> 00:13:56,808
I'm not that kind of guy.

189
00:14:06,401 --> 00:14:09,154
It's natural to feel uneasy
before the wedding.

190
00:14:10,655 --> 00:14:11,906
I'll entertain you instead.

191
00:14:12,907 --> 00:14:14,409
With a hefty cash envelope.

192
00:14:15,034 --> 00:14:17,078
What the heck is that?

193
00:14:17,745 --> 00:14:19,247
How much will you gift me?

194
00:14:26,212 --> 00:14:27,213
Hey.

195
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,777
- What are you doing?
- Hey, Mr. Noh.

196
00:14:50,028 --> 00:14:51,321
Look at that. It's in bloom.

197
00:14:51,738 --> 00:14:53,615
I wonder who's watering
and looking after it.

198
00:14:53,907 --> 00:14:56,576
It's doing so well
in this desolate place.

199
00:14:56,826 --> 00:14:58,828
Gosh, you're very sentimental.

200
00:14:58,912 --> 00:15:00,788
I'm sure you don't care.

201
00:15:00,872 --> 00:15:03,333
Because your life's in full bloom.

202
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:05,293
Ms. Hong from HR just told me.

203
00:15:06,336 --> 00:15:08,630
You might get a special promotion
for catching Director Kang.

204
00:15:08,713 --> 00:15:09,756
Is that true?

205
00:15:11,257 --> 00:15:14,469
- I can't say.
- Wait a minute. I guess it's true.

206
00:15:15,053 --> 00:15:18,765
You were Director Kim's favorite
when he was Head of Audit.

207
00:15:21,017 --> 00:15:23,394
I trust you'll look out for me
later on.

208
00:15:23,478 --> 00:15:24,604
Don't forget that, okay?

209
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:28,233
Guys, have you heard the news?

210
00:15:28,858 --> 00:15:29,859
What news?

211
00:15:29,943 --> 00:15:31,486
People are losing their minds
here and there.

212
00:15:31,569 --> 00:15:33,238
A really scary rumor is going around.

213
00:15:33,321 --> 00:15:34,864
It's code red right now.

214
00:15:34,948 --> 00:15:35,949
What's going on?

215
00:15:38,034 --> 00:15:39,035
Joo In-a

216
00:15:39,911 --> 00:15:40,954
is back.

217
00:15:43,122 --> 00:15:44,123
Isn't that Joo In-a?

218
00:15:44,207 --> 00:15:45,542
- For real?
- It really is her.

219
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,252
HAEMU INTRANET
1 NEW MESSAGE FROM MR. KIM

220
00:15:48,211 --> 00:15:49,587
She must be back.

221
00:15:49,671 --> 00:15:50,797
NEW MESSAGE
NEW NOTIFICATION

222
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,465
What's going on?

223
00:15:52,549 --> 00:15:53,675
YOU GOT A NEW MESSAGE

224
00:15:53,758 --> 00:15:54,759
She actually came back.

225
00:15:55,843 --> 00:15:57,595
- What's happening?
- What do you think?

226
00:15:59,013 --> 00:16:00,265
- Joo In-a's here.
- Joo's here.

227
00:16:00,348 --> 00:16:02,267
- We're done for.
- Is she back for good?

228
00:16:02,350 --> 00:16:03,810
- What a disaster.
- I'll be damned.

229
00:16:05,019 --> 00:16:06,479
I HATE GETTING CC-ED TO EMAILS

230
00:16:06,563 --> 00:16:07,564
WILL OVERSEAS BRANCHES SUFFER?

231
00:16:07,647 --> 00:16:08,690
ALL SITES ARE ON STANDBY

232
00:16:08,773 --> 00:16:09,816
HOW WILL THIS CHANGE THINGS?

233
00:16:09,899 --> 00:16:11,067
I WONDER IF THE EXECUTIVES ARE AFRAID

234
00:16:11,693 --> 00:16:12,944
You know, at work

235
00:16:13,319 --> 00:16:15,238
you must beware
of those with nicknames.

236
00:16:16,239 --> 00:16:19,367
People give nicknames
to badmouth freely.

237
00:16:21,035 --> 00:16:22,996
I bet Joo In-a has

238
00:16:23,955 --> 00:16:25,373
a dozen or so nicknames.

239
00:16:26,082 --> 00:16:28,501
"Joo In-Out" is a famous one.

240
00:16:29,002 --> 00:16:32,463
Get on her bad side and you're out.

241
00:16:33,047 --> 00:16:35,466
I thought that was funny.
"Joo-tergeist."

242
00:16:35,842 --> 00:16:39,012
She's like a poltergeist
that stays at work day and night.

243
00:16:39,929 --> 00:16:42,390
I heard she earned a new nickname

244
00:16:42,473 --> 00:16:44,642
- while working overseas.
- What's that?

245
00:16:44,976 --> 00:16:47,437
She fought a gang
over a business license.

246
00:16:49,939 --> 00:16:50,940
They called her

247
00:16:52,817 --> 00:16:53,901
"Joo-sniper."

248
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:57,363
She actually fired a gun?

249
00:16:57,447 --> 00:16:58,573
I'm sure it's just a rumor.

250
00:16:58,656 --> 00:17:01,117
How could something like that
even become a rumor?

251
00:17:01,409 --> 00:17:02,952
What's most important is

252
00:17:04,287 --> 00:17:06,205
which division she'll join.

253
00:17:07,123 --> 00:17:08,166
Don't you think?

254
00:17:21,095 --> 00:17:22,096
JOO'S IN THE ELEVATOR

255
00:17:22,597 --> 00:17:26,184
KIM JIN-HEE FROM PLANNING:
JOO'S IN THE ELEVATOR

256
00:17:27,018 --> 00:17:28,144
She's in the elevator.

257
00:17:28,227 --> 00:17:29,270
Which floor did she press?

258
00:17:29,604 --> 00:17:30,980
JOO'S IN THE ELEVATOR

259
00:17:31,064 --> 00:17:33,941
WHICH FLOOR DID SHE PRESS?

260
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:38,946
She's smashing the Close Door button.

261
00:17:39,030 --> 00:17:41,991
I think my heart
is getting smashed, too.

262
00:17:43,534 --> 00:17:44,702
Passed the fourth floor.

263
00:17:47,455 --> 00:17:48,456
Fifth floor.

264
00:17:48,956 --> 00:17:50,249
Passed the sixth floor!

265
00:17:53,544 --> 00:17:55,171
Where the heck is she going?

266
00:17:55,505 --> 00:17:56,756
Did HR post a notice?

267
00:17:56,839 --> 00:17:58,007
No, not yet.

268
00:17:58,091 --> 00:17:59,425
HR AND INFORMATION OFFICE

269
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:02,720
HEAD OF HR, HAEMU GROUP
BOO SE-YOUNG

270
00:18:08,518 --> 00:18:10,728
WOULD YOU LIKE TO PROCEED?

271
00:18:10,812 --> 00:18:12,689
APPROVAL OF APPOINTMENT,
JOO IN-A, DEPARTMENT HEAD

272
00:18:12,772 --> 00:18:13,773
CANCEL

273
00:18:13,856 --> 00:18:14,857
APPROVE

274
00:18:17,527 --> 00:18:18,528
Ninth floor.

275
00:18:21,781 --> 00:18:22,824
Tenth floor.

276
00:18:22,907 --> 00:18:24,492
Why does she keep coming up?

277
00:18:25,243 --> 00:18:27,078
AS LONG AS
SHE DOESN'T GET OFF WITH ME

278
00:18:27,161 --> 00:18:29,080
JOO IN-A, PLEASE GET OFF
WHY'S THE ELEVATOR SO SLOW TODAY?

279
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:32,291
PHEW, I'M GETTING OFF FIRST

280
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:33,376
I'M SO JEALOUS

281
00:18:35,336 --> 00:18:36,546
PASSED 13TH FLOOR

282
00:18:36,629 --> 00:18:38,214
WILL SHE GET OFF HERE?

283
00:18:38,297 --> 00:18:39,507
14TH FLOOR...

284
00:19:08,286 --> 00:19:09,328
It's the 14th floor!

285
00:19:18,963 --> 00:19:20,256
Stay calm, everyone!

286
00:19:20,590 --> 00:19:23,134
The Planning Office is
on the 14th floor, too.

287
00:19:24,135 --> 00:19:25,344
PLANNING OFFICE

288
00:19:25,595 --> 00:19:26,596
Put everything away.

289
00:19:26,679 --> 00:19:29,390
Hey, get rid of all the dust.
Wipe every single speck.

290
00:19:29,474 --> 00:19:31,476
Dump all the documents
and scrap papers on your desk.

291
00:19:31,559 --> 00:19:34,896
And your coffees!
Drink it up and dump the cups.

292
00:20:00,338 --> 00:20:01,881
Is there a Kim Gyu-yeong?

293
00:20:05,927 --> 00:20:07,720
ONE-DAY COURIER

294
00:20:08,471 --> 00:20:09,597
What are you doing to me?

295
00:20:16,729 --> 00:20:17,730
It's nice to meet you all.

296
00:20:18,147 --> 00:20:20,399
I'm Joo In-a, the new Head of Audit.

297
00:20:28,157 --> 00:20:31,035
Come on, now.
Why the dull atmosphere?

298
00:20:31,410 --> 00:20:33,204
How about I sing a song
to lighten things up?

299
00:20:40,211 --> 00:20:42,713
Thank you for the warm welcome.

300
00:20:44,215 --> 00:20:45,216
Nice to meet you.

301
00:20:45,758 --> 00:20:47,343
Manager Kwon Myeong-jin.

302
00:20:47,426 --> 00:20:48,761
Yes. I'm pleased to meet you.

303
00:20:49,804 --> 00:20:51,430
You sound overly pleased. Relax.

304
00:20:51,514 --> 00:20:52,932
I will. Sorry.

305
00:20:53,015 --> 00:20:55,142
I'm Mun Gyeong-jin,
assistant team leader of Team One.

306
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:56,894
You're an assistant team leader?

307
00:20:57,228 --> 00:20:59,647
You look young for that title.
I hope we get on well.

308
00:21:00,481 --> 00:21:02,316
I'm Kim Tae-hwan,
Leader of Audit Team Two.

309
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,485
- I hope we can work well.
- I really hope so.

310
00:21:04,569 --> 00:21:05,695
Let's try to get along.

311
00:21:06,529 --> 00:21:08,906
Jeong Dong-min,
assistant team leader of Team Two.

312
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,241
I hope we get along.

313
00:21:10,783 --> 00:21:13,035
I'm Ju Yeon-u,
senior associate of Team One.

314
00:21:13,953 --> 00:21:16,289
Which Ju clan
does your surname belong to?

315
00:21:16,664 --> 00:21:17,665
Well...

316
00:21:17,915 --> 00:21:18,916
Is it from the word "juice"?

317
00:21:19,292 --> 00:21:20,710
Yes, you're right.

318
00:21:22,420 --> 00:21:23,671
I hope we get along.

319
00:21:24,213 --> 00:21:25,840
Wait, she's pretty normal.

320
00:21:25,965 --> 00:21:28,134
There are too many groundless rumors.

321
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:30,595
Right. We got scared for no reason.

322
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:33,472
Hello.

323
00:21:33,556 --> 00:21:35,725
I'm Sung Doo-gi,
a senior associate on Team One.

324
00:21:35,808 --> 00:21:36,851
I hope we work well together!

325
00:21:37,018 --> 00:21:38,269
I love your energy.

326
00:21:38,519 --> 00:21:40,479
- Let's work well together.
- Thank you.

327
00:21:40,563 --> 00:21:42,189
I'm Assistant Manager Ahn Min-su
from the same team.

328
00:21:42,273 --> 00:21:43,399
I hope to impress you.

329
00:21:44,358 --> 00:21:45,902
I look forward
to your impressive work.

330
00:21:46,319 --> 00:21:47,361
Thank you.

331
00:21:50,865 --> 00:21:52,992
Hello, I'm Assistant Manager
Noh Ki-jun of Audit Team One.

332
00:21:56,037 --> 00:21:57,538
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

333
00:22:13,721 --> 00:22:14,764
Shall we get to work?

334
00:22:23,814 --> 00:22:25,566
Excuse me, Ms. Joo?

335
00:22:25,983 --> 00:22:27,485
I'm sorry to bother you
when you just came in.

336
00:22:28,069 --> 00:22:29,946
No problem. Give that to me.

337
00:22:35,826 --> 00:22:37,828
It's a routine audit notification.

338
00:22:37,912 --> 00:22:40,539
I need to send it right away.
Please approve it for me.

339
00:22:40,957 --> 00:22:42,291
Haemu Industries.

340
00:22:42,541 --> 00:22:43,960
You've audited them
for five years in a row.

341
00:22:44,043 --> 00:22:45,044
Yes, that's right.

342
00:22:45,711 --> 00:22:49,298
I've been in charge since my transfer
here from Haemu Industries.

343
00:22:49,382 --> 00:22:51,550
You've been auditing
your former boss for five years.

344
00:22:51,634 --> 00:22:52,635
Yes.

345
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,597
You can stop now.
It must be boring for both parties.

346
00:22:58,224 --> 00:22:59,809
Our new rule that is no one audits

347
00:22:59,892 --> 00:23:01,852
the same subsidiary
for more than two years.

348
00:23:01,936 --> 00:23:03,771
One year if you used to work there.

349
00:23:07,692 --> 00:23:11,195
I get what you're saying, Ms. Joo.

350
00:23:12,029 --> 00:23:14,657
I know better than anyone
how they do business.

351
00:23:15,241 --> 00:23:17,660
I also know
which areas are usually corrupt.

352
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,997
How corrupt is that place
that you couldn't

353
00:23:21,414 --> 00:23:23,207
get to the bottom of it
for five years?

354
00:23:23,708 --> 00:23:24,917
Pardon?

355
00:23:28,087 --> 00:23:29,463
Well, Ms. Joo.

356
00:23:30,089 --> 00:23:31,632
- What I mean is...
- You laughed?

357
00:23:43,936 --> 00:23:45,479
I told you to stop going.

358
00:23:46,731 --> 00:23:48,274
That's all you have to do.

359
00:23:49,316 --> 00:23:50,901
Why do you talk back at every turn?

360
00:23:51,110 --> 00:23:54,155
Do you think I'm here to have
a lengthy discussion with you?

361
00:23:55,322 --> 00:23:57,742
If you know
about Haemu Industries that well

362
00:23:58,075 --> 00:23:59,827
why did you only do
a brief look-over every year?

363
00:24:00,327 --> 00:24:02,288
You haven't found anything
that led to disciplinary action.

364
00:24:03,372 --> 00:24:05,499
You worked there for over ten years.

365
00:24:05,583 --> 00:24:07,418
You just couldn't bear
to punish anyone.

366
00:24:07,501 --> 00:24:09,253
No, it's not that at all.

367
00:24:09,336 --> 00:24:12,757
Then did you collude with them
to hide a sweet slush fund somewhere?

368
00:24:13,132 --> 00:24:14,341
Shall I go digging myself?

369
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:16,802
To see if you audited them
or did business with them?

370
00:24:16,886 --> 00:24:18,721
Why would you
suggest something so dreadful?

371
00:24:18,804 --> 00:24:19,847
If that's not it...

372
00:24:21,015 --> 00:24:23,017
You probably don't take me seriously.

373
00:24:24,226 --> 00:24:25,603
I apologize.

374
00:24:41,035 --> 00:24:42,328
Don't you have any work to do?

375
00:24:47,917 --> 00:24:51,670
I'll speak with each of you
in a one-on-one meeting.

376
00:24:51,754 --> 00:24:53,881
Come to the interview room
when I call your name.

377
00:25:02,014 --> 00:25:03,599
MUN GYEONG-JIN,
CALCULATE SEVERANCE PAY

378
00:25:03,682 --> 00:25:05,309
HOW MUCH TO OPEN
A FRIED CHICKEN STORE?

379
00:25:05,392 --> 00:25:08,395
SHOULD I QUIT?

380
00:25:08,479 --> 00:25:10,231
I WANT TO CRY

381
00:25:10,314 --> 00:25:12,817
INTERVIEW ROOM

382
00:25:23,244 --> 00:25:24,912
Manager Ha Jin-u of Team Two.

383
00:25:35,464 --> 00:25:37,133
It turned into Jurassic Park
in an instant.

384
00:25:39,051 --> 00:25:41,095
Hey, how can you work right now?

385
00:25:41,178 --> 00:25:43,597
Why not? She had a point.

386
00:25:44,682 --> 00:25:46,642
Do specially promoted people
have something in common?

387
00:25:46,725 --> 00:25:48,435
I heard she got promoted three times.

388
00:25:50,855 --> 00:25:53,190
You want to audit
Haemu Pharmaceuticals again?

389
00:25:54,191 --> 00:25:55,860
You're working on something,
aren't you?

390
00:25:56,235 --> 00:25:58,195
What is it? What are they up to?

391
00:25:59,780 --> 00:26:02,241
When I have them
right where I want them

392
00:26:03,492 --> 00:26:04,577
I'll tell you then.

393
00:26:05,369 --> 00:26:06,954
You special promotion jerks.

394
00:26:17,756 --> 00:26:19,592
Can someone get Mr. Ha
a cup of water?

395
00:26:19,884 --> 00:26:20,926
Yes, ma'am.

396
00:26:23,637 --> 00:26:25,139
- I'm useless.
- No, you're not.

397
00:26:36,358 --> 00:26:38,027
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun
of Team One?

398
00:26:40,112 --> 00:26:41,155
Okay.

399
00:26:47,494 --> 00:26:49,496
Our meeting will only
last three minutes.

400
00:26:50,414 --> 00:26:52,875
Good. I'm all for efficient meetings.

401
00:26:54,501 --> 00:26:56,712
Let's see, Assistant Manager Noh.

402
00:26:58,005 --> 00:26:59,340
A pretty favorable evaluation.

403
00:26:59,423 --> 00:27:01,508
You've received top evaluations
ever since you joined Haemu.

404
00:27:02,134 --> 00:27:05,387
- I was lucky.
- So it was all luck.

405
00:27:07,973 --> 00:27:10,976
You've handled only the biggest cases
in each subsidiary.

406
00:27:11,894 --> 00:27:13,520
You closed a lot of big ones.

407
00:27:13,938 --> 00:27:14,980
Yes, my luck

408
00:27:15,689 --> 00:27:17,274
followed as I worked hard.

409
00:27:18,192 --> 00:27:20,945
Let's make a minor change
to your role, Mr. Noh.

410
00:27:21,946 --> 00:27:22,988
A special promotion?

411
00:27:23,697 --> 00:27:24,740
Already?

412
00:27:25,324 --> 00:27:27,618
It's not
personnel evaluation season yet.

413
00:27:27,701 --> 00:27:28,953
That doesn't matter.

414
00:27:29,036 --> 00:27:31,372
Well, if that's what you want,
I'll willingly accept...

415
00:27:31,455 --> 00:27:32,915
I'm sending you to Team Three.

416
00:27:33,749 --> 00:27:34,875
What? To Team Three?

417
00:27:34,959 --> 00:27:37,711
You'll transfer to Team Three
and take over the PM cases.

418
00:27:38,087 --> 00:27:40,256
- "PM" is our code for...
- Personal misconduct.

419
00:27:40,589 --> 00:27:43,175
P for personal and M for misconduct.

420
00:27:43,634 --> 00:27:44,927
They're mostly workplace affairs.

421
00:27:45,552 --> 00:27:47,221
You want me to handle
office scandals?

422
00:27:48,514 --> 00:27:49,515
Yes.

423
00:27:52,851 --> 00:27:55,020
Okay, then. That means

424
00:27:56,188 --> 00:27:57,189
today is your new day one.

425
00:28:04,571 --> 00:28:07,700
Ms. Joo, how could you send me
to Team Three to investigate affairs?

426
00:28:07,992 --> 00:28:09,118
I can't understand why.

427
00:28:09,994 --> 00:28:11,787
Why should I help you understand?

428
00:28:12,121 --> 00:28:13,539
I exercised my right
as your superior.

429
00:28:13,622 --> 00:28:15,874
Yes, that's true. But you admitted

430
00:28:15,958 --> 00:28:17,501
that I performed well every year.

431
00:28:19,503 --> 00:28:20,546
You did great.

432
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:24,341
He's joining us?

433
00:28:25,009 --> 00:28:26,844
I was going to inform you
when things got underway.

434
00:28:26,927 --> 00:28:28,637
I'm working on something
with my team.

435
00:28:29,096 --> 00:28:31,807
It's an important audit
on one of our subsidiaries.

436
00:28:31,890 --> 00:28:33,058
Let me finish it.

437
00:28:33,142 --> 00:28:35,352
Put all the info on our cloud server.

438
00:28:35,436 --> 00:28:37,021
I'll take a look
and allocate someone else.

439
00:28:37,771 --> 00:28:40,482
It follows a complicated logic
and involves many executives.

440
00:28:40,566 --> 00:28:43,027
It requires a very subtle approach.

441
00:28:44,236 --> 00:28:45,362
The only one for the job?

442
00:28:48,115 --> 00:28:49,241
That would be me.

443
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:10,971
Gosh, this is fun.

444
00:29:13,515 --> 00:29:15,517
Mr. Noh, are you that special?

445
00:29:15,726 --> 00:29:17,186
Do you have some kind of superpower?

446
00:29:17,269 --> 00:29:18,896
Can you fly or teleport?

447
00:29:18,979 --> 00:29:20,064
Can you do the palm blast?

448
00:29:20,939 --> 00:29:22,566
Who do you think you are

449
00:29:22,649 --> 00:29:24,902
that you would be the only person
who can do this particular job?

450
00:29:26,487 --> 00:29:27,571
No way.

451
00:29:27,988 --> 00:29:31,033
Do you actually believe
some employees are irreplaceable?

452
00:29:31,575 --> 00:29:33,494
Apple's doing just fine
after Steve Jobs died.

453
00:29:33,869 --> 00:29:35,704
Do you think
a project will collapse without you?

454
00:29:35,788 --> 00:29:36,914
Audit Team 1, of all teams?

455
00:29:38,707 --> 00:29:40,876
How could you be so utterly naive?

456
00:29:41,293 --> 00:29:42,711
Okay, let's say you were mistaken.

457
00:29:43,212 --> 00:29:46,423
How could you voice that to me?

458
00:29:47,091 --> 00:29:48,133
That's plain arrogance.

459
00:29:51,887 --> 00:29:53,305
I'll let you off today
for making me laugh.

460
00:29:53,555 --> 00:29:55,140
Don't go overtime next time.

461
00:29:58,477 --> 00:29:59,937
Give me a reason, at least.

462
00:30:01,647 --> 00:30:04,608
There must be a reason you want me
to handle affairs.

463
00:30:06,485 --> 00:30:07,528
It's because

464
00:30:07,861 --> 00:30:08,862
you are...

465
00:30:11,865 --> 00:30:13,325
the best one for the job.

466
00:30:21,750 --> 00:30:23,419
Hey, what happened?

467
00:30:23,919 --> 00:30:25,712
I thought she was
going to promote you.

468
00:30:25,796 --> 00:30:27,673
Forget the promotion.
This is more like a demotion.

469
00:30:28,549 --> 00:30:31,677
He's going to Team Three
to investigate affairs of all things.

470
00:30:32,177 --> 00:30:33,220
Still.

471
00:30:33,637 --> 00:30:35,305
They're all nice people.

472
00:30:35,806 --> 00:30:39,560
That's true.
Everyone on Team Three is nice.

473
00:30:40,436 --> 00:30:42,062
Do you need help with anything?

474
00:30:45,441 --> 00:30:47,651
- Do you need help?
- They seem nice.

475
00:30:48,110 --> 00:30:49,736
You'll do fine wherever you go.

476
00:30:55,284 --> 00:30:58,370
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun,
the ace of the Audit Team.

477
00:30:58,996 --> 00:31:00,205
Welcome.

478
00:31:00,289 --> 00:31:02,249
How old are you, Mr. Noh?

479
00:31:02,332 --> 00:31:04,126
Still not married?
Or haven't been able to?

480
00:31:04,751 --> 00:31:06,462
The one man here
who gave up on any promotions.

481
00:31:06,753 --> 00:31:08,046
Team Leader Moo Kwang-il.

482
00:31:08,130 --> 00:31:10,090
I heard that people
are reluctant to marry these days.

483
00:31:11,049 --> 00:31:13,552
Consider that a welcome kit.

484
00:31:13,802 --> 00:31:14,845
Look inside.

485
00:31:15,179 --> 00:31:18,265
Bookkeeper Pyun Hae-young
who keeps the team going.

486
00:31:19,516 --> 00:31:20,934
Everything you need is in there.

487
00:31:21,602 --> 00:31:23,729
We usually only give you two pens

488
00:31:23,812 --> 00:31:25,606
but I added one more
out of pity for you.

489
00:31:25,939 --> 00:31:27,816
Once you run out of ink
and need a replacement

490
00:31:27,900 --> 00:31:30,944
you must sign the ledger
before getting a new pen.

491
00:31:31,069 --> 00:31:33,697
Why would you go to such lengths
at a company as big as Haemu?

492
00:31:33,780 --> 00:31:34,865
If you don't like it

493
00:31:35,908 --> 00:31:37,493
blame that fool over there.

494
00:31:38,076 --> 00:31:41,538
You're taking it too far
when all I did was take batteries.

495
00:31:41,622 --> 00:31:44,041
You took a whole pack.

496
00:31:44,124 --> 00:31:47,127
A pack of size AA and AAA each.

497
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:50,255
The guy is always on the lookout
for things to steal

498
00:31:50,672 --> 00:31:51,798
Manager Cha Sung-tae.

499
00:31:52,049 --> 00:31:53,091
Darn it.

500
00:31:53,675 --> 00:31:54,801
Excuse me, Mr. Noh.

501
00:31:54,885 --> 00:31:57,054
Welcome to Team Three.

502
00:31:57,346 --> 00:31:59,056
If there's anything
you need help with

503
00:31:59,139 --> 00:32:00,766
you can come to me at any time.

504
00:32:00,849 --> 00:32:03,060
Senior Associate Baek Hyun-kyu,
who thinks he's a troubleshooter.

505
00:32:03,143 --> 00:32:04,686
He's called "White Blood Cell"
for some reason.

506
00:32:04,770 --> 00:32:07,689
Oh, and before you sit down,
let me adjust your chair for you.

507
00:32:18,450 --> 00:32:21,119
Right! Assistant Manager Yoon Da-yae
is a part of this team.

508
00:32:21,870 --> 00:32:23,288
An SNU graduate with a certified CPA.

509
00:32:23,372 --> 00:32:24,706
The one with crazy credentials!

510
00:32:26,625 --> 00:32:28,126
Hello, Ms. Yoon.

511
00:32:30,087 --> 00:32:31,588
Ms. Yoon has that Gen Z attitude.

512
00:32:32,214 --> 00:32:33,257
You know what Gen Z is, right?

513
00:32:35,050 --> 00:32:36,134
You can't talk to her.

514
00:32:41,515 --> 00:32:44,393
What in the world is nice
about this team?

515
00:32:46,270 --> 00:32:47,354
I can't believe it.

516
00:32:48,063 --> 00:32:49,231
- Stop it, Manager.
- I...

517
00:32:49,314 --> 00:32:50,607
- That's crazy.
- What did I do?

518
00:32:50,691 --> 00:32:51,692
I...

519
00:32:52,442 --> 00:32:54,403
I can't believe
I'm a part of this team!

520
00:32:55,153 --> 00:32:57,155
Even her parents can't talk to her.

521
00:32:57,239 --> 00:32:58,532
- Why did you take this?
- Quiet.

522
00:33:20,679 --> 00:33:22,264
Dinner's ready.

523
00:33:27,144 --> 00:33:28,812
Will he be late again?

524
00:33:32,357 --> 00:33:33,692
HUBBY

525
00:33:40,782 --> 00:33:43,410
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

526
00:33:43,493 --> 00:33:45,746
You will be charged after the beep.

527
00:33:51,918 --> 00:33:54,421
WIFEY

528
00:33:56,882 --> 00:33:57,883
Yes?

529
00:33:58,091 --> 00:33:59,343
Yes, I understand. Goodbye.

530
00:34:00,302 --> 00:34:02,137
- How did it go?
- I talked to them.

531
00:34:02,220 --> 00:34:04,139
- They'll meet the deadline.
- Yes!

532
00:34:04,222 --> 00:34:05,891
Nice job.

533
00:34:05,974 --> 00:34:07,517
You've become good
at pressing the vendors now.

534
00:34:07,601 --> 00:34:08,727
It's all thanks to my teacher.

535
00:34:10,187 --> 00:34:11,355
You're getting a call.

536
00:34:15,233 --> 00:34:16,276
Hey, honey. Yes?

537
00:34:17,444 --> 00:34:19,237
Did I forget to mention?
I have a team dinner tonight.

538
00:34:21,740 --> 00:34:23,450
You're having another team dinner?

539
00:34:23,533 --> 00:34:25,035
Yes, I'm sorry. I've been busy.

540
00:34:25,118 --> 00:34:28,538
Hello, ma'am.
It's Jeong Mi-young speaking.

541
00:34:29,456 --> 00:34:31,416
Yes, hello.

542
00:34:31,625 --> 00:34:33,460
It's been a while
since your husband went home early.

543
00:34:33,543 --> 00:34:35,170
We've been too busy
with the task force.

544
00:34:35,420 --> 00:34:38,215
I'll let him leave
as early as possible today.

545
00:34:40,050 --> 00:34:41,927
Hey, honey.
I'll be home early. I'm sorry.

546
00:34:42,511 --> 00:34:45,097
Okay, don't be too late.

547
00:34:45,555 --> 00:34:46,556
Bye.

548
00:34:49,643 --> 00:34:50,852
Jeez.

549
00:34:59,611 --> 00:35:02,614
Who does she think she is
to let my husband go early?

550
00:35:04,741 --> 00:35:05,826
Darn it.

551
00:35:07,994 --> 00:35:09,037
How dare she?

552
00:35:11,081 --> 00:35:12,249
Who does she think she is?

553
00:35:16,002 --> 00:35:17,003
Damn it.

554
00:35:19,339 --> 00:35:20,841
I've had enough.

555
00:35:25,971 --> 00:35:26,972
Mr. Noh.

556
00:35:27,431 --> 00:35:29,433
These four seats are
the tip-off lines.

557
00:35:29,516 --> 00:35:31,393
You'll get lots of calls

558
00:35:31,852 --> 00:35:33,019
so pick up and accept the reports.

559
00:35:36,356 --> 00:35:37,858
- Yes, okay.
- Okay.

560
00:35:48,618 --> 00:35:49,786
You've reached Audit Team One...

561
00:35:51,163 --> 00:35:52,539
No, Audit Team Three.

562
00:35:52,622 --> 00:35:53,665
Hello.

563
00:35:53,999 --> 00:35:55,959
I'm not sure
if I should be bringing this up

564
00:35:56,418 --> 00:35:58,503
but I'm calling
regarding my team leader.

565
00:36:00,255 --> 00:36:01,882
Yes, I see.

566
00:36:01,965 --> 00:36:04,050
Are you looking
to make an internal report?

567
00:36:04,301 --> 00:36:07,512
I mean, my team leader
keeps farting in the office.

568
00:36:07,763 --> 00:36:10,348
It's a bit too much
to hear it go off all day.

569
00:36:10,432 --> 00:36:12,476
It's the worst office environment!

570
00:36:12,559 --> 00:36:14,519
At least give us an air purifier.

571
00:36:15,353 --> 00:36:16,521
I see.

572
00:36:18,273 --> 00:36:19,691
So your team leader farts?

573
00:36:33,830 --> 00:36:34,956
You've reached Audit Team...

574
00:36:35,540 --> 00:36:38,668
You damn asshole!
What took you so long to pick up?

575
00:36:38,794 --> 00:36:41,421
Yet you get paid a fortune,
don't you, you punk?

576
00:36:41,505 --> 00:36:43,381
- ...Three.
- What Three?

577
00:36:43,465 --> 00:36:45,592
You'll only get a grip
when that business goes down!

578
00:36:45,675 --> 00:36:47,844
- Does your company know you do that?
- Sure.

579
00:36:49,137 --> 00:36:50,889
- What would you like to report?
- Report, my ass!

580
00:36:50,972 --> 00:36:52,432
I'll report your damn life!

581
00:36:52,516 --> 00:36:53,517
What's your name?

582
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,852
I'll talk to your chairman
and tell him all about you!

583
00:36:55,936 --> 00:36:57,604
What the heck is your name?

584
00:36:57,687 --> 00:36:58,980
What's your name?

585
00:37:04,069 --> 00:37:05,654
What are these?

586
00:37:05,737 --> 00:37:07,405
Evidence of infidelity!

587
00:37:07,697 --> 00:37:11,117
I had to go through the trash can
to retrieve those.

588
00:37:11,326 --> 00:37:12,744
Yes, so what are...

589
00:37:21,503 --> 00:37:23,129
Where are you going?

590
00:37:51,241 --> 00:37:52,284
Jeez.

591
00:38:03,086 --> 00:38:05,213
Mr. Noh, are you okay?

592
00:38:05,589 --> 00:38:07,632
You looked pale as you ran in.

593
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:10,552
Is there anyone to pat your back?

594
00:38:11,177 --> 00:38:13,471
If not, I can always come in
for a second.

595
00:38:24,399 --> 00:38:25,567
I'm all right.

596
00:38:28,194 --> 00:38:29,821
Are you sure?

597
00:38:30,405 --> 00:38:33,033
You can take a break
if it's too tough for you.

598
00:38:33,783 --> 00:38:36,411
Nothing beats being healthy.

599
00:38:48,298 --> 00:38:50,133
Let's do proper introductions.

600
00:38:51,092 --> 00:38:53,887
The Head of Audit, Joo In-a.

601
00:38:55,221 --> 00:38:56,681
The former Head of Audit

602
00:38:56,765 --> 00:38:58,642
and the current Director
of Strategic Planning, Kim Han-su.

603
00:38:59,517 --> 00:39:00,644
I've heard a lot about you.

604
00:39:01,686 --> 00:39:02,771
Congratulations on your promotion.

605
00:39:04,314 --> 00:39:05,857
Head of HR, Boo Se-young.

606
00:39:06,608 --> 00:39:07,901
It's been a while, In-a.

607
00:39:10,070 --> 00:39:12,989
We used to work in the same team.

608
00:39:13,615 --> 00:39:14,658
But of course

609
00:39:15,367 --> 00:39:16,660
I started before her.

610
00:39:17,327 --> 00:39:18,536
Hey, Se-young.

611
00:39:18,995 --> 00:39:20,664
You're looking great.

612
00:39:20,997 --> 00:39:22,290
Things must be swell in HR.

613
00:39:26,169 --> 00:39:28,672
You two seem rather close.

614
00:39:29,422 --> 00:39:30,465
That's nice.

615
00:39:30,674 --> 00:39:34,344
This recent appointment was
a genius move, I must say.

616
00:39:35,011 --> 00:39:38,390
We can call our audit teams the sword

617
00:39:38,473 --> 00:39:40,976
of the vice president
and the president.

618
00:39:42,018 --> 00:39:44,604
Someone like Ms. Joo
would be perfect for the job.

619
00:39:45,438 --> 00:39:47,148
Oh, my. How did you know?

620
00:39:49,734 --> 00:39:50,986
I have a knack for swordsmanship.

621
00:39:54,322 --> 00:39:56,408
Ms. Joo has a witty sense of humor.

622
00:39:57,158 --> 00:39:58,702
You'll find it funny
once you get used to it.

623
00:40:01,204 --> 00:40:03,206
How does it feel breathing
the Seoul air again after so long?

624
00:40:03,289 --> 00:40:05,041
The air is the same everywhere.

625
00:40:06,126 --> 00:40:07,919
But the fine dust seems
to have worsened.

626
00:40:09,170 --> 00:40:10,213
So?

627
00:40:11,965 --> 00:40:14,175
Do you regret coming back?

628
00:40:22,559 --> 00:40:23,560
If I do

629
00:40:24,477 --> 00:40:25,895
do I have the option to go back?

630
00:40:44,330 --> 00:40:45,832
Look at the time.

631
00:40:46,291 --> 00:40:47,959
Why don't we grab some dinner...

632
00:40:48,043 --> 00:40:50,128
I have a lot of tasks
to figure out right now.

633
00:40:51,046 --> 00:40:52,088
Why don't we

634
00:40:52,881 --> 00:40:54,049
slice some steak next time?

635
00:40:54,132 --> 00:40:55,133
Yes, sure.

636
00:40:57,260 --> 00:40:58,303
Mr. Vice President.

637
00:40:58,803 --> 00:41:01,014
I'm eating with my parents tonight.

638
00:41:01,097 --> 00:41:02,307
My wife is probably there now.

639
00:41:03,058 --> 00:41:04,476
Goodness, Mr. Vice President.

640
00:41:05,060 --> 00:41:06,436
You're such a romantic.

641
00:41:08,188 --> 00:41:10,565
How's the president doing?

642
00:41:10,899 --> 00:41:12,609
He was discharged last week

643
00:41:12,984 --> 00:41:14,027
but we must keep an eye on him.

644
00:41:15,945 --> 00:41:18,490
I've been
checking his condition frequently.

645
00:42:16,047 --> 00:42:18,466
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected...

646
00:42:26,182 --> 00:42:28,393
- Your call cannot be connected...
- Darn it.

647
00:42:32,772 --> 00:42:34,274
WHY AREN'T YOU ANSWERING MY CALL?
PLEASE CALL ME

648
00:42:34,357 --> 00:42:35,608
Why aren't you picking up?

649
00:42:36,568 --> 00:42:38,653
Please call me.
Why aren't you answering my call?

650
00:42:38,736 --> 00:42:40,196
Give me a call.
Are you still having dinner?

651
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:42,198
Honey, when are you coming home?

652
00:42:42,657 --> 00:42:43,741
When are you coming home?

653
00:42:48,872 --> 00:42:50,206
Damn it!

654
00:42:58,965 --> 00:43:00,216
All right, now.

655
00:43:00,884 --> 00:43:03,219
Our best duo, Mr. Son

656
00:43:03,803 --> 00:43:05,513
and Ms. Jeong.

657
00:43:08,558 --> 00:43:10,226
You know that
the launch of the new brand

658
00:43:10,310 --> 00:43:12,270
will decide the fate
of Haemu Foods, don't you?

659
00:43:12,353 --> 00:43:13,771
- Yes.
- I need you two

660
00:43:13,980 --> 00:43:15,565
to work together
and do your best as a team.

661
00:43:15,648 --> 00:43:17,400
- I'll do my best.
- So will I.

662
00:43:17,483 --> 00:43:18,985
- Can you really do it?
- I'll do my best!

663
00:43:19,068 --> 00:43:20,069
Now, cheers!

664
00:43:20,528 --> 00:43:21,946
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

665
00:43:22,030 --> 00:43:23,031
Let's do this!

666
00:43:23,114 --> 00:43:24,407
- Cheers.
- Good luck.

667
00:43:29,078 --> 00:43:30,121
That's nice.

668
00:43:30,747 --> 00:43:31,915
Did you drink yesterday, too?

669
00:43:31,998 --> 00:43:33,833
I really wanted
to keep myself from drinking tonight.

670
00:43:34,792 --> 00:43:36,211
This meat looks nice.

671
00:43:37,086 --> 00:43:39,005
It's beef we're talking about.

672
00:43:44,219 --> 00:43:47,096
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

673
00:43:47,180 --> 00:43:49,432
- Damn it.
- You will be charged after the beep.

674
00:43:52,644 --> 00:43:53,770
Darn it.

675
00:44:07,158 --> 00:44:08,493
The work is...

676
00:44:10,328 --> 00:44:11,371
Honey!

677
00:44:15,708 --> 00:44:16,793
I'm sorry.

678
00:44:21,547 --> 00:44:22,590
Darn it.

679
00:44:33,059 --> 00:44:34,060
Jeez.

680
00:44:35,687 --> 00:44:37,689
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected...

681
00:45:23,276 --> 00:45:24,777
What the... Open the door.

682
00:45:24,861 --> 00:45:27,030
Hey! Open the door right now!

683
00:45:27,113 --> 00:45:28,114
I'll kill you.

684
00:45:29,032 --> 00:45:31,159
Open the door! Hey!

685
00:45:31,242 --> 00:45:32,243
Honey.

686
00:45:35,872 --> 00:45:36,998
What are you doing?

687
00:46:04,776 --> 00:46:05,777
Heading home now?

688
00:46:10,698 --> 00:46:12,325
He's so out of it.

689
00:46:13,326 --> 00:46:15,495
He's become a different man
in just a day.

690
00:46:46,776 --> 00:46:48,403
- All right!
- All right!

691
00:46:48,486 --> 00:46:49,529
Great job.

692
00:46:50,863 --> 00:46:53,491
ANXIOUSLY WAITING FOR THE RESULT

693
00:46:53,574 --> 00:46:56,077
CHUNG SANG-HYEON
DROPS FROM 2 STARS TO 1 STAR

694
00:46:58,329 --> 00:46:59,956
The accuracy

695
00:47:00,039 --> 00:47:02,667
of your dance dropped quite a lot
in the verse...

696
00:47:04,210 --> 00:47:07,171
No rank lasts forever in this world.

697
00:47:09,215 --> 00:47:10,258
Hence

698
00:47:12,218 --> 00:47:13,845
the higher your ranking

699
00:47:14,554 --> 00:47:15,847
the more anxious you become.

700
00:47:42,498 --> 00:47:43,958
You're such an embarrassment.

701
00:47:44,208 --> 00:47:46,043
How did you know I was there?

702
00:47:46,752 --> 00:47:48,588
Did you snoop around
every restaurant I might be in?

703
00:47:48,921 --> 00:47:50,214
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

704
00:47:50,298 --> 00:47:51,841
I was having a team dinner!

705
00:47:54,427 --> 00:47:56,429
Can't you pick up your phone
while you eat?

706
00:47:56,888 --> 00:47:57,930
My phone?

707
00:47:59,599 --> 00:48:02,351
Right. You're always
cooped up at home.

708
00:48:02,435 --> 00:48:04,270
You wouldn't understand anything
about work life.

709
00:48:04,937 --> 00:48:07,106
You drive me crazy! Damn it.

710
00:48:15,573 --> 00:48:17,325
If you do not wish to remain weak...

711
00:48:19,452 --> 00:48:20,786
you must fight your way up.

712
00:48:46,270 --> 00:48:47,939
What do you mean...

713
00:48:48,022 --> 00:48:49,732
In the end, keeping your rank

714
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:52,902
means survival.

715
00:48:54,904 --> 00:48:56,656
Don't lose heart.

716
00:48:59,116 --> 00:49:00,368
Leave no regrets.

717
00:49:00,910 --> 00:49:04,247
What? How did he not make it?

718
00:49:05,498 --> 00:49:07,792
Not only is he
a good singer and a good dancer

719
00:49:07,875 --> 00:49:09,502
but he's good-looking
and is good at everything!

720
00:49:10,002 --> 00:49:12,713
But he's a total ace.
How did he not make it?

721
00:49:13,464 --> 00:49:14,924
How come?

722
00:49:15,007 --> 00:49:16,342
Why?

723
00:49:58,718 --> 00:49:59,719
Excuse me, Mr. Noh.

724
00:50:01,721 --> 00:50:03,389
She has something to report
to the Audit Team.

725
00:50:04,307 --> 00:50:06,058
She's been waiting
since early morning.

726
00:50:11,439 --> 00:50:12,440
It looks like

727
00:50:13,858 --> 00:50:16,235
my husband is having an affair.

728
00:50:16,319 --> 00:50:17,403
Goodness.

729
00:50:18,362 --> 00:50:20,197
When my husband brought home

730
00:50:20,740 --> 00:50:24,619
perfume as a birthday gift,
I knew something was off.

731
00:50:24,702 --> 00:50:26,370
Wait, what about the perfume?

732
00:50:28,789 --> 00:50:31,584
No one buys a perfume
for a married man.

733
00:50:31,667 --> 00:50:32,918
What do you think that means?

734
00:50:33,461 --> 00:50:36,422
It means she wants to mark him
with that scent.

735
00:50:37,506 --> 00:50:40,801
She wants her man
to smell like something she picked.

736
00:50:41,344 --> 00:50:43,638
I've kept my eyes on my husband
since that day

737
00:50:43,721 --> 00:50:45,556
and he never leaves his phone.

738
00:50:46,015 --> 00:50:47,475
He even takes it into the shower.

739
00:50:47,558 --> 00:50:49,852
I read online that it definitely
means he's having an affair.

740
00:50:52,563 --> 00:50:54,273
And they're always working together.

741
00:50:54,774 --> 00:50:56,651
Not only do they
always go on business trips together

742
00:50:56,734 --> 00:50:58,194
but they even message
each other at night.

743
00:50:59,070 --> 00:51:00,821
Right. I have evidence, too.

744
00:51:13,417 --> 00:51:14,960
It's a strand of hair.

745
00:51:17,129 --> 00:51:18,881
I found it on my husband's shirt.

746
00:51:18,964 --> 00:51:21,550
It must belong to that woman.
I know it.

747
00:51:24,095 --> 00:51:26,055
Ma'am, we can't call this evidence...

748
00:51:26,138 --> 00:51:29,475
We'll investigate
and get back to you right away.

749
00:51:30,351 --> 00:51:31,394
Okay.

750
00:51:36,023 --> 00:51:37,024
What?

751
00:51:37,692 --> 00:51:39,944
We must go through the formalities
after receiving a report.

752
00:51:40,194 --> 00:51:43,114
We have to do the paperwork
and talk to the person in question.

753
00:51:43,739 --> 00:51:45,616
What is it? Go and check.

754
00:51:45,991 --> 00:51:47,034
Go, now.

755
00:51:48,869 --> 00:51:50,413
What am I supposed to check?

756
00:51:50,996 --> 00:51:52,957
Should I run a DNA test
on this hair or what?

757
00:51:55,459 --> 00:51:56,627
Come on.

758
00:52:03,676 --> 00:52:04,802
Anyway

759
00:52:05,177 --> 00:52:07,972
wasn't Mr. Son's wife
really frightening last night?

760
00:52:08,431 --> 00:52:10,433
She came all the way there
just because he didn't pick up.

761
00:52:11,142 --> 00:52:13,185
She apparently suspects something
is going on with Ms. Jeong.

762
00:52:13,644 --> 00:52:15,396
Ms. Jeong must feel so wronged.

763
00:52:15,479 --> 00:52:16,605
All she ever does is work.

764
00:52:17,106 --> 00:52:19,775
But I think I understand why.

765
00:52:20,067 --> 00:52:23,112
Couples only see each other
briefly at night.

766
00:52:23,195 --> 00:52:25,698
But you're with work colleagues
all day long

767
00:52:25,781 --> 00:52:27,616
and share more in common.

768
00:52:27,700 --> 00:52:29,702
And you talk to them much more.

769
00:52:30,286 --> 00:52:32,413
I would be concerned, too.

770
00:52:33,205 --> 00:52:34,457
I don't think I'd like that either.

771
00:52:34,665 --> 00:52:36,375
But there are limits.

772
00:52:36,459 --> 00:52:38,294
She was almost delusional.

773
00:52:39,795 --> 00:52:41,589
Gosh. What is this?

774
00:52:42,506 --> 00:52:43,758
She was infamous.

775
00:52:44,425 --> 00:52:46,886
FOOD BRAND PLANNING TEAM

776
00:52:46,969 --> 00:52:49,221
Director Kang will kill us
if we continue like this.

777
00:52:49,305 --> 00:52:51,432
They're exactly
what we agreed to during the meeting.

778
00:52:51,515 --> 00:52:54,560
- Stop making random changes.
- I don't see the point!

779
00:52:55,144 --> 00:52:57,521
Comparing them with domestic brands
isn't what we're doing.

780
00:52:57,813 --> 00:53:00,441
I kept saying that our focus is
on expanding into the global market!

781
00:53:00,524 --> 00:53:01,984
They're just colleagues.

782
00:53:02,485 --> 00:53:03,527
There isn't any affair.

783
00:53:03,778 --> 00:53:05,237
- What?
- Don't you remember?

784
00:53:08,240 --> 00:53:10,659
Let's analyze all corporations
making under a billion won.

785
00:53:11,202 --> 00:53:13,078
- We have to do this.
- Yes, ma'am.

786
00:53:13,204 --> 00:53:16,248
There are some discrepancies
in the business licenses, so...

787
00:53:16,332 --> 00:53:17,708
I see. Really?

788
00:53:21,754 --> 00:53:24,173
Mr. Noh. Come here. Hurry.

789
00:53:30,179 --> 00:53:31,597
- Are we all here?
- Yes.

790
00:53:32,223 --> 00:53:34,517
All right, then. We received

791
00:53:34,892 --> 00:53:37,853
a very important assignment
directly from the top.

792
00:53:37,937 --> 00:53:39,522
- Our team?
- From the top?

793
00:53:39,605 --> 00:53:41,148
Yes, so that means

794
00:53:41,398 --> 00:53:43,818
we must pause whatever we were doing
and handle this first.

795
00:53:44,109 --> 00:53:46,028
This may turn into a criminal case

796
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:49,073
and blow up into a big story
if anyone outside hears about it.

797
00:53:49,323 --> 00:53:51,200
It must remain confidential

798
00:53:51,784 --> 00:53:54,245
as we resolve the matter
as quietly as possible.

799
00:53:54,328 --> 00:53:55,329
Do you understand?

800
00:53:56,622 --> 00:53:57,706
What is it?

801
00:53:58,082 --> 00:54:00,376
ON-SITE AUDIT TEAM SURVEY
HAEMU GROUP AUDIT TEAM 3

802
00:54:00,668 --> 00:54:01,669
So you're saying

803
00:54:02,086 --> 00:54:03,796
there's poppy here?

804
00:54:03,879 --> 00:54:05,965
Goodness, man.
I told you to be quiet.

805
00:54:07,383 --> 00:54:09,343
The security guard said
he found a poppy out back

806
00:54:09,426 --> 00:54:11,220
while cleaning up the flower bed.

807
00:54:11,303 --> 00:54:12,847
Not the field poppy
but the other kind.

808
00:54:13,264 --> 00:54:15,766
He thinks there may be more
in another place

809
00:54:15,850 --> 00:54:18,561
so we must handle this quietly
before it becomes trouble, okay?

810
00:54:20,521 --> 00:54:21,605
A pharmaceutical company

811
00:54:22,565 --> 00:54:23,607
with a poppy?

812
00:54:24,692 --> 00:54:26,360
Did you eat that flower?

813
00:54:26,861 --> 00:54:28,821
Don't go around eating random stuff
just because it's free.

814
00:54:28,904 --> 00:54:30,656
Goodness. Just keep looking.

815
00:54:39,415 --> 00:54:42,459
- Hello?
- It's Mr. Son's wife calling.

816
00:54:42,543 --> 00:54:44,962
Have you checked the hair?

817
00:54:45,045 --> 00:54:46,964
I'll e-mail you the result.

818
00:54:47,047 --> 00:54:49,133
I'm on a different assignment,
so I must hang up.

819
00:55:02,813 --> 00:55:03,856
Yes?

820
00:55:05,190 --> 00:55:07,651
You said you'd get back to me
after investigating.

821
00:55:08,319 --> 00:55:10,529
I was right, about Ms. Jeong, right?

822
00:55:13,157 --> 00:55:14,950
What will happen to them now?

823
00:55:15,743 --> 00:55:17,661
The company must
handle this strictly to...

824
00:55:17,745 --> 00:55:19,455
Please stop!

825
00:55:21,290 --> 00:55:23,208
Nothing is going on between them.

826
00:55:23,584 --> 00:55:25,961
They're only working hard
even as we speak!

827
00:55:26,045 --> 00:55:27,630
They're together again?

828
00:55:28,756 --> 00:55:30,799
- Did you see them?
- Ma'am.

829
00:55:31,842 --> 00:55:33,719
Please stop pestering me.

830
00:55:34,553 --> 00:55:36,055
You should go see the doctor.

831
00:55:36,138 --> 00:55:39,016
You know, you're being delusional!

832
00:55:53,405 --> 00:55:54,698
You got poop on yourself.

833
00:56:04,124 --> 00:56:05,167
Jeez.

834
00:56:14,718 --> 00:56:16,178
Is the rehearsal
in the conference room?

835
00:56:16,261 --> 00:56:18,180
Yes, I called everyone
and said we were on our way.

836
00:56:18,263 --> 00:56:19,264
- One second.
- Sure.

837
00:56:26,689 --> 00:56:27,731
Thank you.

838
00:56:30,859 --> 00:56:32,361
2. TARGET
SON MYUNG-SOO, JEONG MI-YOUNG

839
00:56:32,444 --> 00:56:34,029
3. METHOD
INTERVIEW, E-MAIL LOGS, CCTV

840
00:57:15,237 --> 00:57:16,655
I hope you bloom and blossom

841
00:57:17,948 --> 00:57:19,450
in this crappy office.

842
00:57:42,431 --> 00:57:44,349
Goodness, Mr. Noh.
Are you getting off now?

843
00:57:49,104 --> 00:57:51,065
I read your report
on Mr. Son Myung-soo's case.

844
00:57:52,149 --> 00:57:53,442
Are you sure that's it?

845
00:57:53,859 --> 00:57:55,652
Are you sure
they aren't having an affair?

846
00:57:56,653 --> 00:57:57,696
No.

847
00:57:58,447 --> 00:58:00,407
How can I be sure
of what's happening between them?

848
00:58:00,824 --> 00:58:02,326
There's no hard evidence

849
00:58:02,659 --> 00:58:04,536
so the circumstantial evidence
points to nothing.

850
00:58:07,623 --> 00:58:09,458
I like how you don't make up crap.

851
00:58:09,917 --> 00:58:13,128
But if this is only between them,
shouldn't you look more into it?

852
00:58:16,423 --> 00:58:17,841
- Hello.
- Hello.

853
00:58:17,925 --> 00:58:20,135
- Food Brand Planning Team?
- Yes.

854
00:58:20,219 --> 00:58:21,428
Are you working overtime?

855
00:58:21,512 --> 00:58:23,806
- Hello.
- Thanks for your hard work.

856
00:58:25,808 --> 00:58:28,602
But I don't see
Mr. Son and Ms. Jeong.

857
00:58:28,685 --> 00:58:30,437
They're getting ready
for the presentation.

858
00:58:30,521 --> 00:58:31,855
We're stepping out to eat dinner.

859
00:58:31,939 --> 00:58:33,398
Is that so?

860
00:58:33,857 --> 00:58:36,110
How do you know everyone in our team?

861
00:58:36,193 --> 00:58:38,320
You're just as they say,
Almighty Joo.

862
00:58:38,737 --> 00:58:41,115
- Almighty Joo?
- It means you have your eyes

863
00:58:41,198 --> 00:58:42,282
on everything and know everything.

864
00:58:42,825 --> 00:58:45,869
Goodness, people say that?
That's crazy.

865
00:58:45,953 --> 00:58:47,287
What? "Almighty Joo"?

866
00:58:48,163 --> 00:58:51,166
But I do know that the Brand Team
is doing something very important.

867
00:58:51,792 --> 00:58:53,961
Okay, since you're all working hard
until late in the night

868
00:58:54,044 --> 00:58:57,589
so I, Almighty Joo, will treat you
to something expensive and delicious!

869
00:58:57,673 --> 00:58:59,133
You are the Almighty Joo!

870
00:59:00,551 --> 00:59:03,011
I'll have it delivered here
for all of you to enjoy

871
00:59:03,095 --> 00:59:04,429
so you can go back upstairs.

872
00:59:04,513 --> 00:59:06,557
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

873
00:59:12,604 --> 00:59:13,647
Good luck.

874
00:59:13,730 --> 00:59:15,149
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

875
00:59:20,445 --> 00:59:22,114
Mr. Noh,
I need a new report from you.

876
00:59:22,322 --> 00:59:23,365
Sorry?

877
00:59:23,448 --> 00:59:26,326
I really must be Almighty Joo.
That's a great nickname.

878
00:59:34,126 --> 00:59:35,711
Why don't we go over our moves again?

879
00:59:37,296 --> 00:59:38,297
Yes, Mr. Son.

880
00:59:43,760 --> 00:59:44,761
But...

881
00:59:50,767 --> 00:59:51,768
what moves do you mean?

882
00:59:58,233 --> 00:59:59,276
Something like this.

883
01:00:20,839 --> 01:00:23,217
What do you mean
you need a new report from me?

884
01:00:23,842 --> 01:00:25,135
You'll find out by tomorrow.

885
01:00:25,636 --> 01:00:27,888
No, maybe today.

886
01:01:01,588 --> 01:01:02,589
Darn it.

887
01:01:15,435 --> 01:01:16,478
Are you all right?

888
01:01:17,688 --> 01:01:18,855
What about you?

889
01:01:20,607 --> 01:01:21,650
What was that?

890
01:01:27,197 --> 01:01:28,282
Darn it.

891
01:01:42,754 --> 01:01:44,006
Mrs. Son...

892
01:01:58,520 --> 01:01:59,563
What did you say?

893
01:02:00,188 --> 01:02:01,231
Delusional?

894
01:02:01,898 --> 01:02:03,025
Damn it.

895
01:02:04,943 --> 01:02:06,945
Why are you only blaming me?

896
01:02:07,821 --> 01:02:10,657
I'm not the one who's crazy.
That asshole and bitch are!

897
01:02:15,454 --> 01:02:16,955
I'm going to kill them.

898
01:02:58,288 --> 01:03:01,208
FILING FOR LOVE

899
01:03:01,792 --> 01:03:04,544
GUEST APPEARANCE
BY PARK HA-SUN, KIM JONG-TAE

900
01:03:29,319 --> 01:03:30,862
Mr. Noh is the pride of our team!

901
01:03:31,822 --> 01:03:33,323
He says you're the pride.

902
01:03:33,407 --> 01:03:34,574
How brazen.

903
01:03:34,658 --> 01:03:36,201
If only everyone else were like you

904
01:03:36,284 --> 01:03:38,995
this world would've been
a much better place.

905
01:03:40,122 --> 01:03:41,415
You're a fool

906
01:03:43,208 --> 01:03:44,793
Do your next assignment right.

907
01:03:44,876 --> 01:03:47,045
It's Zone F in level four
of the basement parking lot.

908
01:03:48,130 --> 01:03:49,923
- We need to expose them.
- Expose?

909
01:03:50,006 --> 01:03:51,758
How am I going to do that?

910
01:03:51,842 --> 01:03:54,428
Morals? Do you think
you're a police officer or a judge?

911
01:03:54,761 --> 01:03:56,304
Do you hate her that much?

912
01:03:56,388 --> 01:03:57,931
Should I just quit?

913
01:03:58,014 --> 01:04:00,976
You should've talked to me
if you wanted to leave the Audit Team

914
01:04:01,184 --> 01:04:02,561
instead of talking behind my back.

915
01:04:17,284 --> 01:04:19,286
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
